The Verilog HDL implementation of a Half Adder can be written as follows: 
reg [1:0] A, B, Sum, CarryOut; 
wire CarryIn; 
assign Sum = A ^ B; 
assign CarryOut = A & B; 
assign CarryIn = (A & !B) | (!A & B);

The Verilog HDL implementation of a Full Adder can be written as follows: 
reg [1:0] A, B, Cin, Sum, CarryOut; 
wire CarryIn; 
assign Sum = (A ^ B ^ Cin); 
assign CarryOut = (A & B & Cin) | ((!A & !B) & Cin) | (A & B & !Cin); 
assign CarryIn = (A & !B & !Cin) | (!A & B & Cin);
